text: Michel Lévêque (born 19 July 1933)Rulers.org is a French diplomat and politician. From 1997 to 2000 he was Minister of State of Monaco. He was the French ambassador to Libya (1985-1989), Morocco (1991-1993), Brazil (1993-1994) and Algeria (1995-1997). ==References== Category:Living people Category:1933 births Category:Ministers of State of Monaco Category:Ambassadors of France
